{
  "title": "Problems with Twitter",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "03c2500cf49857e2",
      "text": "Particular problems with Twitter, especially from 2016 onwards after the introduction of algorithmic timelines were:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b7a6000d0fca7148",
      "text": "* Centralised"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "feaeb1da3d540351",
      "text": "* Proprietary, so forking and doing something better wasn't an option"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "44a6b09abfb5ac00",
      "text": "* They forced you to ID yourself with a phone number"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "e9dcf35f862e9c22",
      "text": "* They handed your data to third party companies"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f200f1e19ea39666",
      "text": "* Most governments were using it to ID people saying bad things about them"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d51c7924b137aa2a",
      "text": "* Ads and corporate campaigns"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9066b4e18d421141",
      "text": "* Heavy handed censorship, or refusal to remove users who were violating TOS merely because of their celebrity status"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d18ab73c631d05a9",
      "text": "* Refusal to deal with obvious bot accounts, used for spying or creating an economy of fake followers"
    }
  ],
